\par }\pard \s58\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2323119 {\f1\insrsid2323119\charrsid2323119 Dear brethren and sisters in the Lord, faithful children of our Russian Church Abroad!
\line 
\par From 
7-12 December of this year, at Holy Protection Church in Nyack, a Pan-Diaspora Conference of the Clergy of the Russian Orthodox Church Abroad will be held, and thereafter, from 13-16 December, the Council of Bishops of the Russian Orthodox Church Outside 
of Russia will meet.
\par At the Conference, as well as at the Council of Bishops, there will be discussed very important questions concerning the path of our Church. We, the archpastors and clergy, are clearly aware that without the help of God it will be impos
sible to resolve any questions at all. For this reason, I entreat you, the faithful and dutiful children of our Church, to intensify your prayers during the Pan-Diaspora Conference and the Council of Bishops, that both meetings will proceed in an edifying
 spirit, in peace and oneness of mind, for the good of the Church of Russia.
\par I ask that each member of our Church pray during his private prayers for the success of the Conference and the Council. This prayer may be accompanied with a prostration or prostra
tions; it may include the reading of an akathist hymn; or one may simply pray in one's own words.
\par I ask the clergy, before leaving for the Conference, after the Divine Liturgy, to insert in the Reiterate Litany the special petitions invoking the Holy Spiri
t upon the archpastors and pastors, and after the service to announce to their parishioners the impending Conference and Council, to read the prayer at the end of the Service of Supplication, calling upon the aid of the Holy Spirit before the beginning of
 every good work, and to urge the parishioners to pray.\line 
\par During the council, I ask that every priest, if possible, serve daily, either at home or in church, the Service of Supplication to the Savior, the Mother of God, the New Martyrs, or the Holy Hierarch 
and Wonder-worker John of Shanghai and San Francisco. Thus, beloved in the Lord, you will be able to take part, spiritually and prayerfully, in the conciliar life of our Church.\line 
\par }\pard \s58\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2323119 {\cs60\b\f1\fs20\insrsid2323119\charrsid2323119 +Metropolitan Laurus}{\f1\fs20\insrsid2323119\charrsid2323119 \line }{
\cs61\i\f1\fs20\insrsid2323119\charrsid2323119 4 December 2003}{\insrsid2323119\charrsid2323119 
